The 7-Step Blueprint to Build a 7-Figure Agency 📈

Listen, starting an agency is tough.

But it's an incredibly rewarding business.

I've coached over 3000+ agency owners.

And helped 80+ of them hit 6 and even 7-figures in their agencies.

But I'm not just another coach. I've walked the walk, scaling my own agency Affluent .co to 7-figures.

So here are the 7 fundamental tactics that led to my agency's 7-figure success:

----

1️⃣ Start Local

Your location is your secret weapon when starting out.

It's often the only reason someone will listen to you.

It's often the only reason someone will listen to you.

Here's what you do:

• Use Google Maps to list local businesses

• Cross off anyone who's not a good fit

• Call 20 leads a day - it'll take about two hours

Do the math: 1 meeting a day = 5 a week = 20 a month.

Keep at it until you've got enough clients.

Most people never make these calls. That's why they don't see results.

----

2️⃣ Don't Pick One Niche Right Away

Look, beginners often make two mistakes:

• They pick the most popular (and saturated) niche

• Or they stick to one niche and miss other opportunities

Instead, try working with 3-5 clients in different industries.

For example: You might discover you prefer gyms over real estate agents.

Or maybe you'll find a blue ocean niche no one's tapped into.

The goal? FIND your niche, don't just pick one blindly.

----

3️⃣ Input = Output

Here's the deal: agencies thrive on sales.

More outreach = More meetings = More client

It's that simple.

You don't need fancy strategies or a killer website to start.

Just figure out how much time you can dedicate daily.

Then do as much outreach as possible in that time.

Stick to it, and watch the results roll in.

----

4️⃣ Outreach Is Everything

When you're new, nobody knows you.

So knock on some doors - literally and figuratively.

I'm talking cold calls and face-to-face meetings.

So knock on some doors - literally and figuratively.

I'm talking cold calls and face-to-face meetings.

Sure, DMs and emails work too.

But they usually get average results.

Do what others won't, and you'll stand out.

----

5️⃣ Collect Leverage

You're starting from scratch, right?

So obsess over getting results for your clients.

Start with one killer case study.

Use that to get referrals, then more case studies.

Soon you'll have testimonials, great ads, and a website full of reviews.

That's how you build authority and unlock new levels of opportunity.

----

6️⃣ It's All About You Until It Isn't

Here's the truth: you need to be a high performer to attract other high performers.

At first, all you have is your time and a dream.

At first, all you have is your time and a dream.

Maximize that time. Do everything to achieve that dream.

But once you're maxed out, bring in others to leverage their time.

----

7️⃣ Systemize Everything

Want to scale? You can't be holding everyone's hand.

Document everything. Create SOPs for all processes.

Automate what you can, delegate what you can't.

This is how you grow without losing your mind.

----

7 Deadly Sales Call Mistakes 😬 - Avoid or Stay Broke!

If you're making 3 or more of these errors on your sales calls, your agency will crash and burn.

But don't panic!

Here's how you can identify these 7 mistakes and more importantly, how to avoid them...

----

1️⃣ Poor frame control:

Frame control is all about setting the tone and direction of the conversation.

When you enter a sales call, it's crucial to establish a clear agenda, guide the discussion with targeted questions, and redirect any off-topic discussions.

Remember, how you enter the call is how you leave the call.

If you don't take the lead, you'll likely lose the sale.

Remember, how you enter the call is how you leave the call.

If you don't take the lead, you'll likely lose the sale.

----

2️⃣ Selling features instead of benefits:

Customers want to know how your offer will make their lives better, solve their problems, and make things easier.

If you're going to talk about a feature, follow up with an attached benefit.

They aren't looking for fancy features alone.

----

3️⃣ Reading from a script:

Clients are looking for genuine connections, not to sit on a Zoom call and talk to a robot.

When you rely too heavily on a script, you miss out on the opportunity to build rapport and truly understand your prospect's needs.

Instead of reciting lines, focus on actively listening and having an engaging conversation.

Instead of reciting lines, focus on actively listening and having an engaging conversation.

----

4️⃣ Not digging deep enough:

During discovery calls, you need to gather as much information as possible about your prospect's situation.

Ask questions like: 

- What's the main problem you're facing right now? 
- How long has this issue persisted?
- What have you already done to try and fix this?

By learning about your prospect's needs and pain points, you'll be better equipped to offer a tailored solution.

Remember, you can't solve a puzzle with missing pieces.

----

5️⃣ Confusing offers:

If your offer is unclear or confusing, prospects will hesitate to buy, and you'll frequently hear them say, "I'll think about it."

To avoid this, make sure to craft a clear, concise offer that outlines the key benefits and avoids using technical jargon.

Clarity is king when it comes to closing deals.

----

6️⃣ Demo dilemma:

A lack of preparation can lead to a disjointed, unconvincing presentation.

To ensure a smooth demo, close any unrelated tabs, have only your presentation open, and guide your client through the presentation using your mouse.

This will help keep your prospect engaged and focused on your offer.

----

7️⃣ Lack of conviction:

Confidence is key when it comes to closing clients.

If you don't believe in your own offer, your prospects will sense that uncertainty and doubt the value of your services.

The best way to build conviction is by stacking undeniable proof in your favor.

The best way to build conviction is by stacking undeniable proof in your favor.

This could include case studies, testimonials, or data-driven results.

By demonstrating your expertise and track record or proof of concept, you'll show prospects that you are who you say you are.

You need to convince the prospect that you actually know what you're talking about!

With shorter days and cold weather approaching, the winter months can often have a negative impact on people’s mental health and well-being.

Multiple studies have shown the importance of good mental health in business, with bad mental health leading to decreased productivity, decreased enthusiasm, poor communication with colleagues, and overall reduced ability to complete physically and mentally demanding tasks. 

Here are a few tips to help you with your mental health and well-being throughout the winter.

- Increase exposure to natural light
- Eat healthy and balanced meals
- Improve your sleep hygiene
- Exercise in moderation
- Do more of what you enjoy
- Consider investing in therapy

We describe a growth mindset as a pattern where we embrace challenges and view failure “not as evidence of unintelligence but as a springboard for growth and for stretching our existing abilities. 

While a fixed mindset grips onto the belief that intelligence and talents are static, and success is accomplished solely based on talent and little effort.

It goes without saying that everyone, not just professionals, should strive for a growth mindset. However, that is not an easy feat without some of the tools to get there. 

Here are some of our top tips to get you started 🔽

1. Allow yourself to dream
2. Acknowledge and embrace imperfections
3. Try one new thing every day
4. Be your own cheerleader
5. Cultivate a sense of purpose
